## Core Modules

### AATP™ — Authorship & Origin Proof
- Establishes provenance and traceability
- Anchors authorship at creation

---

### MCCL™ — Cryptographic Continuity Layer
Ensures artifact survivability across time using:
- Hash identity (SHA-256)
- Timestamp anchoring (RFC-3161)
- Optional blockchain anchoring
- Continuity verification

---

### MCEC™ — Chain of Custody Engine *(Planned)*
Tracks:
- Storage history
- Access logs
- Transfer events
- Custody verification

---

### MVRL™ — Verification & Replay Layer *(Partial)*
Implements:
- Re-hash validation
- Replay verification
- Independent audit pathways

---

### MABL™ — Admissibility Bridge Layer *(Planned)*
Maps:
- Technical artifacts → legal admissibility
- Evidence → institutional acceptance

---

### MEPL™ — Evidence Presentation Layer *(Planned)*
Handles:
- Exhibit generation
- Binder formatting
- Filing-ready outputs

---

## Canonical Principle

Cryptographic proof ≠ evidentiary truth

All artifacts must pass through:

Identity → Time → Continuity → Verification → Interpretation → Admissibility

